\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces NM-MPOD operator hierarchy. The three names describe the mathematical content of the reduced vector-field library, not the decoder. All three variants use the same nonlinear split decoder $\mathbf  u\approx \mathbf  u_{\mathrm  {ref}}+\mathbf  V\bm  {q}+\bar  {\mathbf  V}\mathcal  {N}(\bm  {q},\bm  {\mu })$.}}{12}{table.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:nmmpod_hierarchy}{{2}{12}{NM-MPOD operator hierarchy. The three names describe the mathematical content of the reduced vector-field library, not the decoder. All three variants use the same nonlinear split decoder $\bu \approx \uref +\bV \bq +\Vbar \Nmap (\bq ,\bmu )$}{table.caption.2}{}}
